Exercice 2

2) (2 points) Let V be a partition of an undirected graph \(G\). For every community \(X_r\in \mathcal{V}\), let \(a_r\) be the fraction of edges incident to nodes in \(X_r\), and for every \(Xr,Xs \in \mathcal{V}\), let \(e_{r,s}\) be the fraction of edges in \(G\) that link nodes in \(X_r\) with nodes in \(X_s\).


Segons larticle Finding community structure in very large networks que podem trobar aqu, tenim que

\[ \begin{array}{rcl} a_r &=& \displaystyle \frac{1}{2m} \sum_{v_i \in X_r} \mbox{deg}(v_i),\\ e_{rs} &=& \displaystyle \frac{1}{2m} \sum_{V_i\in \mathcal{X}_r,V_j\in \mathcal{X}_s} a_{ij}, \end{array} \] on \(a_{ij}\) s lement \((i,j)\) de la matriu dadjacncia.


    (a) Write an expression for the modularity \(Q(\mathcal{V})\) of the partition \(\mathcal{V}\) in terms of these quantities ar and \(e_{r,s}\).

    Segons larticle esmentat, la modularitat es pot expresar com

    \[ Q(\mathcal{V})=\sum_{\mathcal{X}_r \in \mathcal{V}} \left( e_{rr} - a_r^2 \right). \]

    Vegem-ho.


    Tenim que,

    \[ Q(\mathcal{V})= \frac{1}{2m} \sum_{\mathcal{X}_r \in \mathcal{V}} \sum_{\{V_i,V_j\} \subseteq\mathcal{X}_r} \left( a_{ij} - \frac{\mbox{deg}(v_i)\mbox{deg}(v_j)}{2m} \right). \]

    Que podem reescriure com,

    \[ Q(\mathcal{V})= \sum_{\mathcal{X}_r\in \mathcal{V}} \left( \frac{1}{2m} \sum_{\{V_i,V_j\} \subseteq\mathcal{X}_r} a_{ij} - \sum_{\{V_i,V_j\} \subseteq\mathcal{X}_r} \frac{\mbox{deg}(v_i)\mbox{deg}(v_j)}{(2m)^2} \right). \]

    A ms, tenim que

    \[ e_{rr}=\frac{1}{2m} \sum_{\{V_i,V_j\} \subseteq\mathcal{X}_r} a_{ij}. \]

    Per tant,

    \[ \begin{array}{rcl} Q(\mathcal{V}) &=& \displaystyle \sum_{\mathcal{X}_r\in \mathcal{V}} \left( e_{rr} - \sum_{\{V_i,V_j\} \subseteq\mathcal{X}_r} \frac{\mbox{deg}(v_i)\mbox{deg}(v_j)}{(2m)^2} \right)\\ \\ &=& \displaystyle \sum_{\mathcal{X}_r\in \mathcal{V}} \left( e_{rr} - \frac{ \sum_{\{V_i,V_j\} \subseteq\mathcal{X}_r} \mbox{deg}(v_i)\mbox{deg}(v_j)}{(2m)^2} \right). \end{array} \]

    Daltra banda,

    \[ \sum_{\{V_i,V_j\} \subseteq\mathcal{X}_r} \mbox{deg}(v_i)\mbox{deg}(v_j) = \sum_{V_i \in\mathcal{X}_r} \mbox{deg}^2(v_i) + \sum_{\{V_i,V_j\} \subseteq\mathcal{X}_r :\ i\not=j} 2 \mbox{deg}(v_i)\mbox{deg}(v_j) = \left( \sum_{V_i \in\mathcal{X}_r} \mbox{deg}(v_i) \right)^2, \]

    on la primera igualtat es dna perqu contam doble, s a dir, sumam els graus \(\mbox{deg}(v_i)\mbox{deg}(v_i)\), \(\mbox{deg}(v_j)\mbox{deg}(v_j),\) \(\mbox{deg}(v_i)\mbox{deg}(v_j)\) i \(\mbox{deg}(v_j)\mbox{deg}(v_i)\).

    Finalment, obtenim el que volem demostrar tal com segueix.

    \[ \begin{array}{rcl} Q(\mathcal{V}) &=& \displaystyle \sum_{\mathcal{X}_r\in \mathcal{V}} \left( e_{rr} - \left( \frac{ \sum_{V_i \in\mathcal{X}_r} \mbox{deg}(v_i)}{2m} \right)^2 \right)\\ \\ &=&\displaystyle \sum_{\mathcal{X}_r \in \mathcal{V}} \left( e_{rr} - a_r^2 \right). \end{array} \]

    (b) In the AMEN (AIDS in Multi-Ethnic Neighborhoods) study (1992), the following frequencies of ethnicities in a large sample of heterosexual couples in San Francisco were recorded.


    Women

    Black 0.258 0.016 0.035 0.013 0.323

    White 0.013 0.023 0.306 0.035 0.377
    Other 0.005 0.007 0.024 0.016 0.053

    Consider the undirected network of relationships for the sample studied and the partition defined by the nodes ethnicity (black, hispanic, white, and other). Compute the modularity of this partition. Assuming that the sample was representative of their community, what can you conclude about ethnic homophily in this community?

    Donada la informaci de la taula, emprarem la frmula en a) per calcular la modularitat. Si ens fixam, a la diagonal de la taula tenim la fracci darestes en el graf que ajunten nodes de la mateixa tnia, per tant, \(e_{r,r}\). Ara considerem, per exemple, la primera fila; el primer valor s \(e_{B,B}\), el segon ens indica la fracci de dones hispniques que sn la parella dun home negre i els segents el mateix per la corresponent tnia. A ms, recordem que \(a_{B}=\frac{1}{2m}\sum_{v_i\in \mathcal{X}_B} \mbox{deg}(v_i)\), per tant, per fer \(a_{B}\) contam les arestes dins la comunitat \(\mathcal{X}_B\) dos cops i les que arriben duna altra comunitat a aquesta un sol cop; desprs dividim entre \(2m\). s a dir, volem la proporci darestes dins \(a_{B}\) dos cops, ms la proporci de les que arriben duna altra comunitat un cop; tot entre \(2\). Aix, s sumar la fila \(1\) ms la columna \(2\) i dividir el resultat entre \(2\); en aquest exemple.


    Per tant, podem calcular la modularitat tal com segueix.


    Primer, calculam tots els \(e_{r,r}\) i \(a_r\).

    #Vector (eBB, eHH, eWW, eOO), la diagonal.
err=c(0.258, 0.157,0.306, 0.016)

sum_rows=c(0.323,0.247,0.377,0.053)

ar=(sum_rows+sum_cols)/2

    modularity=sum(err-ar^2)

Exercice 3

3) (2 points) Consider the configuration model where a fraction \(p_1\) of nodes have degree \(1\) and the remaining fraction of nodes \(p_3 = 1-p_1\) have degree \(3\). Let us consider, to fix ideas, networks of order \(n = 10^4\).

    (a) Take first \(p_1 = 0.5\), \(p_3 = 0.5\). Estimate through a simulation the expected fraction of a network of order \(n = 10^4\) covered by its largest component.

    Volem crear una mostra de grafs aleatris que segueixin un model de configuraci amb la meitat dels nodes \(1\) i la meitat \(3\); ja que prenem \(p_1=p_2=0.5\). Aix, cream la distrubuci de graus del nostre graf dorde \(n = 10^4\) tal com segueix.

    degreeDist=c(rep(1, (10^4)/2), rep(3, (10^4)/2))

    Ara, ja podem introduir la distribuci de graus a sample_degseq i obtenir una mostra amb la mida de ma major component conexa de cada graf. Una vegada tinguem aquest valor, podem calcular la mitjana de la mida.

    N=1000
sample=replicate (N, sort(components(sample_degseq(degreeDist, method="simple.no.multiple"))$csize,decreasing = TRUE)[1])

#expected fraction covered by its largest component
E_L1=mean(sample)/10^4
E_L1
    ## [1] 0.8150862

    Com podem observar, la major part dels nodes formen part de la major component connexa.

    (b) Now, plot a graph of the expected fraction (estimated through simulations) of a network of order \(n = 10^4\) covered by its largest component for values of \(p_1\) from \(0\) to \(1\) in \(0.01\) steps. According to your graph, what is the probability \(p_1\) at which the giant component disappears? Is your estimate consistent with the theory?

    En aquest apartat, calcularem la fracci que representa la component connexa ms gran esperada per diversos valors de \(p_1\), de forma anloga a lapartat anterior. Guardam els valors esperats obtinguts per a cada \(p_1\) a la variable EL1_list. De la mateixa manera, guardarem la mida relativa esperada de la segona major component a la variable EL2_list, i aix podrem comparar les mides.

    N=100
EL1_list=c()
EL2_list=c()
for( p in seq(0,1,by=0.01)){
  cat(p/0.01," ")
  #Distribuci per cada p
  degreeDist=c( rep(1, floor(p*(10^4)) ), rep(3, 10^4-floor(p*(10^4)) ) )
  #Cream les mostres i guardam la esperana de L1 i L2
  sample_L1=c()
  sample_L2=c()
  for(i in 1:N){
    components=sort(components(sample_degseq(degreeDist,
                  method="simple.no.multiple"))$csize,decreasing = TRUE)
    L1=components[1]
    L2=components[2]
    sample_L1=c(sample_L1,L1)
    sample_L2=c(sample_L2,L2)
  }
  EL1_list=c(EL1_list,mean(sample_L1)/10^4)
  EL2_list=c(EL2_list,mean(sample_L2)/10^4)
}

    A continuaci, dibuixam els valors esperats en funci de \(p_1\) per cada una de les components.

    plot(seq(0,1,by=0.01),EL1_list, xlab = "p1",ylab = "Expected fraction", ylim = c(0,1),
     pch=21, col="green4", bg="mediumspringgreen")
par(new=TRUE)
plot(seq(0,1,by=0.01),EL2_list,xlab = "p1",ylab = "Expected fraction",ylim = c(0,1),
     pch=21, col="blue", bg="deepskyblue")
abline(v=0.63, col="lightcoral")
legend("topright", inset=.02, c("L1","L2"), col=c("green4","deepskyblue"), pch=c(19,19), cex=0.8)

    Si ens fixam noms a la grfica de L1, tenim que partir de \(p_1=0.75\), aproximadament, no hi ha gaire diferncia en el nombre esperat de nodes de les dues components majors del graf. Per tant, aqu ja no hi ha cap dubte de que la component connexa gegant ha desaparegut.

    La teoria ens diu que, si \(E(\mbox{deg}^2)>2E(\mbox{deg})\), el graf t una component connexa gegant i les altres components tenen ordre com a molt \(log(10^4)\approx 9\), aix s de lordre de \(10^-3\) en termes relatius. Vegem fin quina \(p_1\) es dna la condici.

    Sigui \(P_d(k)\) la distribuci dels graus, s a dir, la fracci de nodes de grau \(k\), tenim que \(P_d(1)=p_1\) i \(P_d(3)=p_3=1-p_1\). A ms, considerem \(n_1\) el nombre de nodes de grau \(1\) i \(n_3\) el nombre de nodes de grau \(3\). Aix, \[ \begin{array}{rcllcl} 2E(\mbox{deg})&=& \displaystyle 2 \sum_{k} k\cdot P_d(k) &=& \displaystyle\ 2\left[ \sum_{k=1}^{n_1} 1p_1 + \sum_{k=1}^{n_3} 3(1-p_1) \right] = 2n_1p_1 + 6n_3(1-p_1),\\ E(\mbox{deg}^2)&=& \displaystyle 2 \sum_{k} k^2\cdot P_d(k) &=& \displaystyle 2\left[ \sum_{k=1}^{n_1} 1p_1 + \sum_{k=1}^{n_3} 9(1-p_1) \right] = n_1p_1 + 9n_3(1-p_1). \end{array} \]


    Ara, teim que \(n_1=p_110^4\) i \(n_3=10^4(1-p_1)\). Per tant,

    \[ \begin{array}{rcl} 2E(\mbox{deg})&=& \displaystyle 2\cdot10^4(p_1^2 + 3(1-p_1)^2),\\ E(\mbox{deg}^2)&=& 10^4(p_1^2 + 9(1-p_1)^2) \displaystyle . \end{array} \]


    Volem veure fins quin \(p_1\) es satisf \(E(\mbox{deg}^2)>2E(\mbox{deg})\), equivalentment \(E(\mbox{deg}^2)-2E(\mbox{deg})>0\). En termes de \(p_1\) es

    \[ E(\mbox{deg}^2)-2E(\mbox{deg})= 2p_1^2 - 6p_1 + 2p_1^2 > 0. \]


    Aix, si estudiam el signe del polinomi \(2p_1^2 - 6p_1 + 2p_1^2\) obtenim que entre \(p_1=0\) i $ p_1=0.634$ s positiu, per tant, existeix component connexa gegant.

    Daquesta manera, pels pasos \(p\) agafats en la simulaci, hauriem dobtenir que hi ha component connexa gegant almenys fins el \(0.063\). Aix, sha dibuixat la lnea vertical vermella en \(p_1=0.063\) i, com sobserva, la component connexa major t gaireb el \(60\%\) dels nodes, mentre que la fracci esperada de la segona est molt prxima al \(0\) (per dalt). Daquesta manera, si consideram fora gran el \(55\%\) dels nodes, com lordre de la segona major component es tan petit, tenim que la simulaci sajusta amb la teoria, ja que fins \(p_1=0.063\) hi ha component connexa gegant, i desprs la fracci de nodes de la primera component disminueix rpidament el seu valor.


Exercice 4

4) (4 points) Stochastic models can be used to predict links in a network. Now, in a homework you were asked to produce an ERGM of Greys Anatomy sexual contact network. Using your model (or a friends, if you did not deliver this homework):

Abans de respondre els apartats segents, recordem el model ERG emprat per les relacions de Greys Anatomy.

Primer, carregam les dades dels personatges de la srie i cream la xarxa amb els seus atributs, tal com es va fer al Handout 8.

GA_nodes=read.table("GA_nodes.txt", header=TRUE)
GA_edges=read.table("GA_edges.txt")

#Cream graf.
GA=graph_from_data_frame(GA_edges, directed = FALSE)

#Afegim els atributs.
order=as.numeric(V(GA)$name)

V(GA)$label<-as.character(GA_nodes$name)[order]
V(GA)$name<- as.character(GA_nodes$name)[order]
V(GA)$sex<-as.character(GA_nodes$sex)[order]
V(GA)$birthyear<-GA_nodes$birthyear[order]
V(GA)$race<-as.character(GA_nodes$race)[order]
V(GA)$position<-as.character(GA_nodes$position)[order]
V(GA)$season<-GA_nodes$season[order]
V(GA)$sign<-as.character(GA_nodes$sign)[order]

#Ho pasam a tipus "network" per poder emprar ERGM.
GAnetwork=as.network(as.matrix(as_adjacency_matrix(GA)),directed=FALSE)
V(GA)$sex=as.factor(V(GA)$sex)
network::set.vertex.attribute(GAnetwork,"sex", V(GA)$sex)
network::set.vertex.attribute(GAnetwork,"birthyear", V(GA)$birthyear)
network::set.vertex.attribute(GAnetwork,"race", V(GA)$race)
network::set.vertex.attribute(GAnetwork,"position", V(GA)$position)
network::set.vertex.attribute(GAnetwork,"season", V(GA)$season)
network::set.vertex.attribute(GAnetwork,"sign", V(GA)$sign)

Cream el model amb les variables escollides.

mod=ergm(GAnetwork ~ nodematch("sex") + degree(1) + absdiff("birthyear") +
          nodematch("race") + absdiff("season"))

Per tant, el model resultant s \[ \begin{array}{rcl} \log\left( \frac{P(A_{ij}=1|G_{ij}^c)}{P(A_{ij}=0|G_{ij}^c)}\right) &=& -3.38330 \cdot \Delta(\mbox{nombre de relacions homosexuals})+ 2.23563 \cdot \Delta(\mbox{nombre de nodes de grau 1})\\ && -0.14660 \cdot \Delta(\mbox{suma diferncies d'edat entre nodes adjacents})\\ && +0.62716 \cdot \Delta(\mbox{nombre de relacions entre mateixa raa})\\ && -0.30320 \cdot \Delta(\mbox{suma diferncies en el nombre de la temporada}),\\ \end{array} \] on recordem que,

    No sha trobat ninguna aresa amb aquestes condicions, aleshores, anem a calcular la probabilitat de que existeixi laresta per cada aresta del graf.

    Cream la funci que calcula el logartme de odds, segons lestimaci lineal obtinguda.

    log_odds <- function(u,v, degree){
  coef=mod$coef
  coef['nodematch.sex']*(ifelse(V(GA)[u]$sex==V(GA)[u]$sex, 1, 0)) +
    coef['degree1']*(ifelse( (degree[u]==2 ) & (degree[u]==2) , 2, 0)) + #2 perque no contam l'aresta uv
    coef['degree1']*(ifelse( xor(degree[u]==2, degree[u]==2), 1, 0)) +
    coef['absdiff.birthyear']*abs( V(GA)[u]$birthyear-V(GA)[v]$birthyear ) + 
    coef['nodematch.race']*(ifelse(V(GA)[u]$race==V(GA)[u]$race, 1, 0)) +
    coef['absdiff.season']*abs( V(GA)[u]$season-V(GA)[v]$season ) 
}

    Ara, per a cada aresta, calculam la probabilitat de que existeixi emprant la funci anterior. Un cop tenim totes les probabilitats ens quedam amb el mxim i cercam les parelles amb aquesta probabilitat.

    degree=degree(GA)
edges=get.edgelist(GA)
log_odds_list=c()
for( i in 1:nrow(edges)){
  u=edges[i,1]
  v=edges[i,2]
  lo=log_odds(u,v,degree)
  log_odds_list=c(log_odds_list, exp(lo)/(1+exp(lo)) )
}
cat(" max:",max(log_odds_list),"\n", "row in edges:", which(log_odds_list==max(log_odds_list)))

    V(GA)$sex<-as.character(GA_nodes$sex)[order]

  for( female in which(V(GA)$sex=="F")){
    
    if( !(female %in% neighbors(GA,male)) & (V(GA)[male]$race==V(GA)[female]$race) &
        (degree(GA)[male]==1) & (degree(GA)[female]==1)&
        (V(GA)[male]$birthyear==V(GA)[female]$birthyear)){
          cat(male,"-",female,":",V(GA)[male]$name,"and",V(GA)[female]$name,"\n")
        }
  }
}
